def: A genus of trilobites found in the Silurian and Devonianformations. Phacops bufo is one of the most common species.

An open square in a European town, especially an Italian town;hence (Arch.), an arcaded and roofed gallery; a portico. In theUnited States the word is popularly applied to a veranda.We walk by the obelisk, and meditate in piazzas. Jer. Taylor.
A written confession of faith; a formal statement of foctrines.
Having finished the course of life; dead; deceased. "Defunctorgans." Shak.The boar, defunct, lay tripped up, near. Byron.
An outbuilding for washing, esp. one for washing clothes; alaundry.
A game at cards in which the object is to make fifteen points.
Of or pertaining to the saxicavas.-- n.
The state or quality of being old; old age.
A merman; the male of the mermaid. [R.] "Not to mentionmermaids or seamen." Locke.
A group of the Carnivora, which includes the cats, civets, andhyenas.
